# ABL DTB chain — ARMADA / ROCKNIX slot order (from armada-boot-partition/KERNEL).
#
# ROCKNIX-ABL picks chain[index] for the stored device model. MaSi used the wrong
# permutation (0=Odin2, 1=Mini, 2=Portal…) — ARMADA uses:
#   1=Portal, 2=Odin2, 3=Mini, 4=Thor, 5–6=RP6
# Slot 0 = other SoC (Odin3) in ARMADA; kept as reference blob for index alignment.
# Slots 7–8 = other handhelds; 9–12 = qcom,qcs8550 generic fallbacks.
#
# Extract reference blobs once: ./scripts/extract-armada-dtb-chain.sh
#
# SLOT|SOURCE|FILE|DEVICE
0|reference|slot-00.dtb|slot0-ref
1|kbuild|qcs8550-ayn-odin2portal.dtb|portal
2|kbuild|qcs8550-ayn-odin2.dtb|odin2
3|kbuild|qcs8550-ayn-odin2mini.dtb|mini
4|kbuild|qcs8550-ayn-thor.dtb|thor
5|kbuild|qcs8550-retroidpocket-rp6.dtb|rp6
6|kbuild|qcs8550-retroidpocket-rp6.dtb|rp6-alt
7|reference|slot-07.dtb|slot7-ref
8|reference|slot-08.dtb|slot8-ref
9|reference|slot-09.dtb|qcom-generic
10|reference|slot-10.dtb|qcom-generic2
11|reference|slot-11.dtb|qcom-generic3
12|reference|slot-12.dtb|qcom-generic4
13|reference|slot-13.dtb|generic-tail
